Defendant Erin L Maloney in court with Attorney Nicole M Masnica.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Lucas Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts #1 & 2 of amended information.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Counts #1 & 2 on amended information.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Masnica makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  2 Days jail - (2 days credit)  **TIME SERVED**

       Costs/surcharges are waived

COUNT #2:  FINE:  $704.00  & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($500.00) and remainder due to be paid at $50.00 per month, commencing 6/1/15, alternate 8 days jail if not paid)
